               <p>SAMUEL WRIGHT. I am a <rs id="t18170416-217-viclabel1147" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-217-victim1605 t18170416-217-viclabel1147"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18170416-217-crimeloc1148">Mutton-lane, Clerkenwell-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170416-217-crimeloc1148" type="placeName" value="Mutton-lane, Clerkenwell-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170416-217-crimeloc1148" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-217-off1145 t18170416-217-crimeloc1148"></join>. On the 15th of April, the prisoner, and another man, came into my shop about six o'clock in the evening, the other man came to pledge a candlestick-the prisoner stood against the door, by the trowsers; I saw him put something under his coat, and asked him what he had got there - He said, "nothing."<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181704160060"></xptr>I took the trowsers from under his coat, and secured him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
